#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""agent-msg: CLI for delivering async messages to running Claude Code agents.

Originally a stub that documented the SendMessage gap; now an actual delivery
mechanism implemented on top of the obligations system. Each spawned agent
gets:
  - An inbox JSON file at ~/.config/claude/agent-inbox/<agent_id>.json (0o600)
  - A GATE-MODE obligation registered against tool_pattern '*' that runs the
    `agent_inbox_empty` predicate against that file. The obligation is scoped
    to subagents only via `all_of [is_main_loop {negate: true}, ...]` so the
    main loop never sees its own banner; only the spawned agent does. The
    `agent-msg ack`, `agent-msg inbox`, `agent-msg gc`, and `agent-msg disarm`
    calls are registered as `exempt_patterns` so the agent can clear /
    inspect / teardown its own inbox without the gate firing on those calls.

Schema (version 2, 2026-05-01):
    {
      "schema_version": 2,
      "messages": [
        { "id":      "m-...",        # short opaque id
          "from":    "...",
          "ts":      "ISO8601 UTC",
          "queue_item": "...|null",
          "text":    "body",
          "read":    false,           # flipped to true by `ack`
          "read_at": null              # ISO8601 set when read=true
        },
        ...
      ]
    }

Legacy (pre-v2) inboxes are bare JSON arrays of messages with no read/id
fields; they are auto-migrated on first read (every message gets read=false +
a synthetic id + missing-field defaults). Bare-string entries (defensive
fallback) become a message with text=<body>, read=false. We never delete
content during migration -- the migration is purely additive.

Persistence + GC:
    - `send` appends an unread message; messages stay on disk after `ack`.
    - `ack` flips read=true + sets read_at; the message body is preserved
      so the agent can re-read it later via `inbox --all`.
    - `inbox` defaults to UNREAD only; `--all` shows read messages too.
    - Every CLI invocation runs an implicit GC pass that drops messages
      whose read_at is older than AGENT_MSG_TTL_HOURS (default 24h).
      Explicit `agent-msg gc <agent_id>` is also available.

Why GATE mode (was inform mode 2026-04-28 -> 2026-04-30): empirical evidence
shows the inform-mode stderr banner does NOT reach spawned subagents in any
way that affects their reasoning. Two consecutive test agents on
2026-04-30 (aad6cb28, aa3634cd) had a verified `agent-msg send` deliver to
their inbox, ran to completion, and never called `agent-msg ack` -- the
inbox still held the unread message at agent-completion. The stderr banner
either gets filtered out of the subagent's tool-result stream or arrives
but is treated as ignorable noise. Gate-mode HARD-DENIES every tool call
from the subagent while the inbox is non-empty, with the message contents
in the deny banner -- that's impossible to ignore because the agent's tool
call literally fails until they call ack.

When a message is delivered (`agent-msg send <id> <text>`), the inbox grows
by one entry. On the agent's next non-exempt tool call, the PreToolUse
obligations gate hook fires, evaluates the `agent_inbox_empty` predicate
(which now fails), and DENIES the call with a banner containing the message
contents. The agent reads the banner, processes the message, and runs
`agent-msg ack <id>` (which is on the exempt list, so it always passes) to
clear the inbox. The obligation persists across acks so future `send`s also
surface; the predicate naturally flips back to satisfied once the inbox
holds [].

Subcommand surface:
  agent-msg list                   — show currently tracked agents (index)
  agent-msg show <id>              — show metadata for one agent
  agent-msg index register <id>    — add an agent to the index (no inbox)
  agent-msg index done <id>        — drop an agent from the index
  agent-msg arm <id>               — initialise inbox + register inform-mode obligation
  agent-msg disarm <id>            — clear inbox + remove obligation
  agent-msg send <id> <text>       — append a message to <id>'s inbox
  agent-msg send --queue-id q-XXXX <text>
                                   — resolve the q-id to its single LIVE agent
                                     then send (errors on zero / multiple live)
  agent-msg resolve <q-id>         — print the live agent id bound to a queue id
                                     (--all lists every match incl. stale)
  agent-msg whoami <id>            — reverse lookup: print the q-id bound to <id>
  agent-msg inbox <id>             — read inbox; default UNREAD only (--all shows read too)
  agent-msg ack <id>               — flip every UNREAD message to read=true (keeps body)
  agent-msg gc <id>                — drop read messages older than the TTL
  agent-msg gc-dead                — satisfy inbox obligations for agents no longer alive
  agent-msg --test                 — run embedded test suite

Auto-disarm note (2026-05-03):
    Claude Code's PostToolUse hook for the Agent tool fires only on the
    synchronous-launch reply (status="async_launched"), never on actual
    subagent termination. Subagents in this codebase are async-launched,
    so the disarm path of post-tool-agent-arm-hook never runs and inbox
    obligations leak until the 4h TTL expires. q-0162 (PR #82) made the
    leaks harmless via agent_id scoping on the agent_inbox_empty leaf,
    but the rows still bloat the obligations DB. `agent-msg gc-dead`
    sweeps them: it cross-references each inbox obligation's owning
    agent_id against `claude-watch active-agents --json` and satisfies
    obligations whose owner is no longer alive. It also fires
    opportunistically (rate-limited) at the top of every CLI invocation
    via _maybe_implicit_gc_dead so the cleanup happens organically; an
    explicit cron is optional.

The inbox path is overridable via --inbox-dir for testing; the default
location is ~/.config/claude/agent-inbox/.

State files:
  ~/.config/claude/active-agents.json   — agent index (existing)
  ~/.config/claude/agent-inbox/<id>.json — per-agent inbox (new)
"""

from __future__ import annotations

import argparse
import fcntl
import json
import os
import re
import secrets
import subprocess
import sys
import time
from datetime import datetime, timezone
from pathlib import Path

CONFIG_DIR = Path.home() / ".config" / "claude"
INDEX_FILE = CONFIG_DIR / "active-agents.json"
INBOX_DIR = CONFIG_DIR / "agent-inbox"
INDEX_MODE = 0o600
INBOX_MODE = 0o600

# Inbox JSON schema version. v1 was a bare list of message dicts (no
# read/id fields); v2 wraps the list in {schema_version, messages} and
# adds id/read/read_at to each entry.
INBOX_SCHEMA_VERSION = 2

# Default TTL for the per-agent inform-mode obligation. 4 hours is plenty
# for a typical agent run; the disarm path tears it down explicitly when
# the agent finishes, so this only matters if the main loop forgets.
DEFAULT_OBLIGATION_TTL_SECS = 4 * 3600

# Default TTL for read messages: 24 hours after read_at. Override via the
# AGENT_MSG_TTL_HOURS env var (float; values <= 0 disable GC).
DEFAULT_READ_TTL_HOURS = 24.0


def _read_ttl_hours() -> float:
    """Return the read-message TTL in hours, honoring AGENT_MSG_TTL_HOURS."""
    raw = os.environ.get("AGENT_MSG_TTL_HOURS", "").strip()
    if not raw:
        return DEFAULT_READ_TTL_HOURS
    try:
        return float(raw)
    except ValueError:
        return DEFAULT_READ_TTL_HOURS


def _new_msg_id() -> str:
    """Short opaque id for an inbox message: m-<8 hex>."""
    return "m-" + secrets.token_hex(4)

# Identifier prefix used in the obligation's deny_message so we can find
# the obligation later via `obligations list --json` and remove it on
# disarm. We don't have a stable obligation id (those are random) so we
# match on this marker substring.
OBLIGATION_TAG_PREFIX = "agent-msg/inbox:"


def _now_iso() -> str:
    return datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()


def _ensure_config_dir() -> None:
    CONFIG_DIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
    INDEX_FILE.touch(mode=INDEX_MODE, exist_ok=True)
    try:
        INDEX_FILE.chmod(INDEX_MODE)
    except OSError:
        pass


# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Index I/O (lightly locked; same pattern as before)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------


def _read_index() -> dict:
    _ensure_config_dir()
    if not INDEX_FILE.exists() or INDEX_FILE.stat().st_size == 0:
        return {}
    try:
        with open(INDEX_FILE, "r", encoding="utf-8") as fh:
            fcntl.flock(fh.fileno(), fcntl.LOCK_SH)
            try:
                data = json.load(fh)
            finally:
                fcntl.flock(fh.fileno(), fcntl.LOCK_UN)
        return data if isinstance(data, dict) else {}
    except (json.JSONDecodeError, OSError):
        return {}


def _write_index(data: dict) -> None:
    _ensure_config_dir()
    with open(INDEX_FILE, "w", encoding="utf-8") as fh:
        fcntl.flock(fh.fileno(), fcntl.LOCK_EX)
        try:
            json.dump(data, fh, indent=2)
            fh.flush()
            try:
                os.fsync(fh.fileno())
            except OSError:
                pass
        finally:
            fcntl.flock(fh.fileno(), fcntl.LOCK_UN)
    try:
        INDEX_FILE.chmod(INDEX_MODE)
    except OSError:
        pass


# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Inbox path helpers
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------


def _inbox_dir(args=None) -> Path:
    """Resolve inbox directory: --inbox-dir override, else env var, else default."""
    if args is not None and getattr(args, "inbox_dir", None):
        return Path(os.path.expanduser(args.inbox_dir))
    env_override = os.environ.get("AGENT_MSG_INBOX_DIR", "").strip()
    if env_override:
        return Path(os.path.expanduser(env_override))
    return INBOX_DIR


def _inbox_path(agent_id: str, args=None) -> Path:
    return _inbox_dir(args) / f"{agent_id}.json"


def _ensure_inbox_dir(args=None) -> Path:
    d = _inbox_dir(args)
    d.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
    try:
        d.chmod(0o700)
    except OSError:
        pass
    return d


# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Schema migration + locked inbox I/O (atomic append)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------


def _normalise_message(entry, *, default_ts: str | None = None) -> dict:
    """Coerce a raw inbox entry into a v2 message dict.

    Accepts:
      * dict -- merged onto defaults (missing fields get sensible defaults)
      * str  -- treated as a bare body string (defensive fallback)
      * other -- coerced via repr() into the body field

    The migration is purely additive: we never drop fields, only fill in
    missing ones. read defaults to False and read_at to None so legacy
    messages surface as unread on first contact -- the agent is free to
    ack them and they'll move to read=true with the present timestamp.
    """
    base = {
        "id": None,
        "from": "?",
        "ts": default_ts or _now_iso(),
        "queue_item": None,
        "text": "",
        "read": False,
        "read_at": None,
    }
    if isinstance(entry, dict):
        base.update(entry)
    elif isinstance(entry, str):
        base["text"] = entry
    else:
        base["text"] = repr(entry)
    if not base.get("id"):
        base["id"] = _new_msg_id()
    if not isinstance(base.get("read"), bool):
        base["read"] = False
    if not base.get("ts"):
        base["ts"] = _now_iso()
    if base.get("read") and not base.get("read_at"):
        base["read_at"] = _now_iso()
    return base


def _coerce_inbox(raw_data) -> tuple[list, bool]:
    """Coerce a parsed JSON value into a v2 message list.

    Returns (messages, migrated). `migrated` is True iff the input was not
    already a v2 envelope, signalling that the caller should rewrite the
    file in v2 form to lock in the migration.
    """
    if isinstance(raw_data, dict):
        version = raw_data.get("schema_version")
        msgs = raw_data.get("messages", [])
        if not isinstance(msgs, list):
            return [], True
        if version == INBOX_SCHEMA_VERSION:
            # Even on a v2 envelope, run each entry through normalisation
            # so any partially-written entries get filled in.
            normalised = [_normalise_message(m) for m in msgs]
            # Detect whether any normalisation actually changed anything;
            # if so, we still want to flush the cleaned form to disk.
            migrated = any(
                normalised[i] != msgs[i] if isinstance(msgs[i], dict) else True
                for i in range(len(msgs))
            )
            return normalised, migrated
        # Older v? envelope -- migrate.
        return [_normalise_message(m) for m in msgs], True
    if isinstance(raw_data, list):
        # v1 (bare list of messages or strings).
        return [_normalise_message(m) for m in raw_data], True
    # Unrecognised shape -- treat as empty (keeps the default-open
    # contract for the predicate; caller will overwrite cleanly).
    return [], True


def _read_inbox_locked(path: Path) -> tuple:
    """Open + LOCK_EX. Returns (fh, list_of_v2_messages). Caller must call
    _write_inbox_locked or _unlock_inbox.

    The on-disk format is the v2 envelope {schema_version, messages}; this
    function transparently auto-migrates v1 (bare list) and other shapes
    on read, returning a v2 message list to the caller.
    """
    path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
    fd = os.open(str(path), os.O_RDWR | os.O_CREAT, INBOX_MODE)
    fh = os.fdopen(fd, "r+", encoding="utf-8")
    fcntl.flock(fh.fileno(), fcntl.LOCK_EX)
    fh.seek(0)
    raw = fh.read()
    if not raw.strip():
        return fh, []
    try:
        data = json.loads(raw)
    except json.JSONDecodeError:
        # Treat malformed as empty so we don't blackhole. We'll overwrite
        # cleanly on the next write.
        return fh, []
    msgs, _migrated = _coerce_inbox(data)
    return fh, msgs


def _write_inbox_locked(fh, messages: list) -> None:
    """Write the v2 envelope back to disk, then release the lock."""
    envelope = {
        "schema_version": INBOX_SCHEMA_VERSION,
        "messages": messages,
    }
    fh.seek(0)
    fh.truncate()
    fh.write(json.dumps(envelope, indent=2) + "\n")
    fh.flush()
    try:
        os.fsync(fh.fileno())
    except OSError:
        pass
    fcntl.flock(fh.fileno(), fcntl.LOCK_UN)
    fh.close()


def _unlock_inbox(fh) -> None:
    try:
        fcntl.flock(fh.fileno(), fcntl.LOCK_UN)
    except OSError:
        pass
    try:
        fh.close()
    except OSError:
        pass


# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Garbage-collection: drop read messages whose read_at is older than the
# configured TTL. Returns (kept, dropped) message lists -- the caller
# decides whether to flush to disk.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------


def _gc_messages(messages: list, *, ttl_hours: float | None = None,
                 now_ts: float | None = None) -> tuple[list, list]:
    """Split `messages` into (kept, dropped) by read_at age.

    A message is dropped iff:
      * it is read (read=true)
      * has a parseable read_at
      * read_at is older than ttl_hours (default from env / 24h)

    Unread messages, messages with no read_at, and messages whose read_at
    is unparseable are always kept. ttl_hours <= 0 disables GC entirely.
    """
    if ttl_hours is None:
        ttl_hours = _read_ttl_hours()
    if ttl_hours <= 0:
        return list(messages), []
    if now_ts is None:
        now_ts = datetime.now(timezone.utc).timestamp()
    cutoff = now_ts - (ttl_hours * 3600)
    kept = []
    dropped = []
    for m in messages:
        if not isinstance(m, dict):
            kept.append(m)
            continue
        if not m.get("read"):
            kept.append(m)
            continue
        read_at = m.get("read_at")
        if not isinstance(read_at, str) or not read_at:
            # Read but no read_at -- keep (we don't know how old it is).
            kept.append(m)
            continue
        try:
            ts = datetime.fromisoformat(read_at).timestamp()
        except (ValueError, TypeError):
            kept.append(m)
            continue
        if ts < cutoff:
            dropped.append(m)
        else:
            kept.append(m)
    return kept, dropped


def _gc_inbox_path(path: Path, *, ttl_hours: float | None = None) -> tuple[int, int]:
    """Run a GC pass on a single inbox path. Returns (kept, dropped).

    Idempotent + safe to call on every CLI invocation. Skips silently if
    the inbox file is missing.
    """
    if not path.exists():
        return 0, 0
    try:
        fh, messages = _read_inbox_locked(path)
    except OSError:
        return 0, 0
    try:
        kept, dropped = _gc_messages(messages, ttl_hours=ttl_hours)
        if dropped or len(kept) != len(messages):
            _write_inbox_locked(fh, kept)
        else:
            _unlock_inbox(fh)
    except Exception:
        _unlock_inbox(fh)
        raise
    return len(kept), len(dropped)


def _maybe_implicit_gc(args=None) -> None:
    """Best-effort sweep of every inbox in the inbox dir.

    Runs at the top of every CLI invocation so an agent that's been
    quiet for a while still trims its own inbox. Errors are swallowed
    -- GC must never block a send/ack/inbox call.

    Also opportunistically calls ``_maybe_implicit_gc_dead`` to sweep
    obligation rows belonging to no-longer-alive subagents (rate-limited
    via a debounce file so the claude-watch shell-out doesn't fire on
    every CLI call).
    """
    try:
        d = _inbox_dir(args)
        if not d.exists():
            return
        for child in d.iterdir():
            if child.suffix != ".json":
                continue
            try:
                _gc_inbox_path(child)
            except Exception:
                continue
    except Exception:
        pass
    # Rate-limited dead-agent sweep. Errors swallowed.
    try:
        _maybe_implicit_gc_dead(args)
    except Exception:
        return


# Debounce / rate-limit for the dead-agent obligation sweep. The sweep
# shells out to claude-watch (not free), so we cap it to once per
# AGENT_MSG_GC_DEAD_INTERVAL_SECS (default 300s = 5 min). Override via
# env var for tests / tighter cadence. Set to <= 0 to disable the
# implicit sweep entirely (explicit `agent-msg gc-dead` still works).
DEFAULT_GC_DEAD_INTERVAL_SECS = 300

# Inbox-dir-relative debounce stamp file. Living in the inbox dir keeps
# it isolated when tests override AGENT_MSG_INBOX_DIR.
GC_DEAD_STAMP_FILENAME = ".gc-dead.stamp"

# Liveness window (seconds) passed to `claude-watch active-agents
# --max-age-seconds` when deciding which agents are DEAD for gc purposes.
#
# This is DELIBERATELY much larger than claude-watch's own 120s default
# (`DEFAULT_AGENT_ALIVE_MAX_AGE_SECS`). That 120s window answers a
# different question — "is the main loop legitimately blocked by a child
# right now" — and is appropriately short. Reusing it for gc-dead was a
# latent bug: a subagent that simply goes quiet for >120s (a long thinking
# pass, a slow Bash/tool call, or waiting on a backgrounded child) is NOT
# dead, yet active-agents reports alive=false and the sweeper would then
# unlink its inbox + satisfy its obligation OUT FROM UNDER the still-running
# agent — silently defeating every main-loop->subagent redirection.
#
# gc-dead's job is only to reap obligations LEAKED by agents that exited
# long ago; the 4h obligation TTL is the real backstop, so this window can
# be generously large. 30 min is comfortably above any realistic in-turn
# quiet gap while still cleaning up genuinely-dead agents well before TTL.
# Override via AGENT_MSG_GC_ALIVE_MAX_AGE_SECS.
DEFAULT_GC_ALIVE_MAX_AGE_SECS = 1800


def _gc_alive_max_age_secs() -> int:
    raw = os.environ.get("AGENT_MSG_GC_ALIVE_MAX_AGE_SECS", "").strip()
    if not raw:
        return DEFAULT_GC_ALIVE_MAX_AGE_SECS
    try:
        val = int(float(raw))
    except ValueError:
        return DEFAULT_GC_ALIVE_MAX_AGE_SECS
    return val if val > 0 else DEFAULT_GC_ALIVE_MAX_AGE_SECS


def _gc_dead_interval_secs() -> int:
    raw = os.environ.get("AGENT_MSG_GC_DEAD_INTERVAL_SECS", "").strip()
    if not raw:
        return DEFAULT_GC_DEAD_INTERVAL_SECS
    try:
        return int(float(raw))
    except ValueError:
        return DEFAULT_GC_DEAD_INTERVAL_SECS


def _maybe_implicit_gc_dead(args=None) -> None:
    """If enough time has passed since the last sweep, run gc-dead."""
    interval = _gc_dead_interval_secs()
    if interval <= 0:
        return
    try:
        d = _inbox_dir(args)
        d.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
        stamp = d / GC_DEAD_STAMP_FILENAME
        now = time.time()
        try:
            last = stamp.stat().st_mtime
        except FileNotFoundError:
            last = 0.0
        if (now - last) < interval:
            return
        # Touch first so a long sweep doesn't pile up parallel callers.
        stamp.touch()
        try:
            os.utime(stamp, (now, now))
        except OSError:
            pass
        _gc_dead_obligations(dry_run=False, args=args)
    except Exception:
        return


# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Dead-agent obligation sweeper
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------


def _claude_watch_cli() -> str | None:
    """Resolve claude-watch CLI path. Tests override via env var."""
    override = os.environ.get("AGENT_MSG_CLAUDE_WATCH_CLI", "").strip()
    if override:
        return override if os.path.exists(override) else None
    import shutil
    found = shutil.which("claude-watch")
    return found  # may be None


def _alive_agent_ids() -> set[str] | None:
    """Query claude-watch active-agents and return the set of alive agent_ids.

    Returns None if the CLI is unavailable or returns malformed output.
    Callers MUST treat None as "can't determine" and refuse to GC -- a
    transient claude-watch outage must never silently nuke live
    obligations.
    """
    cli = _claude_watch_cli()
    if not cli:
        return None
    # Use a generous liveness window for gc purposes (see
    # DEFAULT_GC_ALIVE_MAX_AGE_SECS): an agent quiet for >120s is NOT dead,
    # and reaping its inbox/obligation while it is still running is the bug
    # this guards against. Older claude-watch builds without the
    # `--max-age-seconds` flag ignore the extra arg gracefully? No — clap
    # would reject an unknown arg, so fall back to a bare query if the
    # flagged invocation fails (returncode != 0 / spawn error).
    max_age = _gc_alive_max_age_secs()
    try:
        proc = subprocess.run(
            [cli, "active-agents", "--json",
             "--max-age-seconds", str(max_age)],
            capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=10, check=False,
        )
        if proc.returncode != 0:
            # Possibly an older claude-watch that lacks --max-age-seconds.
            # Retry without the flag rather than treating the whole query
            # as a failure (which would refuse to GC forever).
            proc = subprocess.run(
                [cli, "active-agents", "--json"],
                capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=10, check=False,
            )
    except (FileNotFoundError, subprocess.TimeoutExpired, OSError):
        return None
    if proc.returncode != 0:
        return None
    try:
        data = json.loads(proc.stdout)
    except (json.JSONDecodeError, ValueError):
        return None
    agents = data.get("agents") if isinstance(data, dict) else None
    if not isinstance(agents, list):
        return None
    alive: set[str] = set()
    for entry in agents:
        if not isinstance(entry, dict):
            continue
        if entry.get("alive") is True:
            aid = entry.get("agent_id")
            if isinstance(aid, str) and aid:
                alive.add(aid)
    return alive


def _agent_id_from_obligation(ob: dict) -> str | None:
    """Pull agent_id from an inbox-style obligation row.

    Two sources, in priority order:
      1. ``deny_message`` shape ``agent-msg/inbox:<agent_id>``.
      2. ``predicate.params.predicates[*].params.agent_id`` on the
         ``agent_inbox_empty`` leaf (q-0162's scoping field).

    Returns None if neither is present / parseable.
    """
    deny = ob.get("deny_message") or ""
    if isinstance(deny, str) and deny.startswith(OBLIGATION_TAG_PREFIX):
        candidate = deny[len(OBLIGATION_TAG_PREFIX):].strip()
        if candidate:
            return candidate
    pred = ob.get("predicate") or {}
    if isinstance(pred, dict):
        params = pred.get("params") or {}
        leaves = params.get("predicates") if isinstance(params, dict) else None
        if isinstance(leaves, list):
            for leaf in leaves:
                if not isinstance(leaf, dict):
                    continue
                if leaf.get("kind") != "agent_inbox_empty":
                    continue
                lp = leaf.get("params") or {}
                if isinstance(lp, dict):
                    aid = lp.get("agent_id")
                    if isinstance(aid, str) and aid:
                        return aid
    return None


def _is_inbox_obligation(ob: dict) -> bool:
    """True iff this obligation is one of ours (created by `agent-msg arm`)."""
    deny = ob.get("deny_message") or ""
    return isinstance(deny, str) and deny.startswith(OBLIGATION_TAG_PREFIX)


def _gc_dead_obligations(dry_run: bool = False,
                          args=None) -> dict:
    """Walk every inbox obligation; satisfy any whose owning agent is dead.

    Default-open contract: if claude-watch can't be queried, return early
    with reason="claude-watch-unavailable" and DO NOT touch any
    obligations. The 4h TTL safety belt remains the backstop.

    Returns a dict shape:
        {
          "ok": bool,
          "reason": str | None,            # None on success
          "alive_count": int,              # alive agent_ids known
          "checked": int,                  # inbox obligations inspected
          "dead": [
            {"agent_id": "...", "obligation_id": "...",
             "satisfied": bool, "inbox_removed": bool}
          ],
          "skipped_unparseable": int,      # obs we couldn't extract agent_id from
          "dry_run": bool,
        }
    """
    alive = _alive_agent_ids()
    if alive is None:
        return {
            "ok": False,
            "reason": "claude-watch-unavailable",
            "alive_count": 0,
            "checked": 0,
            "dead": [],
            "skipped_unparseable": 0,
            "dry_run": dry_run,
        }
    obligations = _list_obligations()
    cli = _obligations_cli()
    dead_records: list[dict] = []
    skipped = 0
    checked = 0
    for ob in obligations:
        if not isinstance(ob, dict) or not _is_inbox_obligation(ob):
            continue
        checked += 1
        agent_id = _agent_id_from_obligation(ob)
        if not agent_id:
            skipped += 1
            continue
        if agent_id in alive:
            continue
        ob_id = ob.get("id")
        record = {
            "agent_id": agent_id,
            "obligation_id": ob_id,
            "satisfied": False,
            "inbox_removed": False,
        }
        if not dry_run and cli and ob_id:
            try:
                proc = subprocess.run(
                    [cli, "satisfy", ob_id],
                    capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=10, check=False,
                )
                if proc.returncode == 0:
                    record["satisfied"] = True
            except (FileNotFoundError, subprocess.TimeoutExpired, OSError):
                pass
            # Best-effort: also unlink the inbox file (matches what
            # cmd_disarm would have done if the disarm path actually
            # ran). Errors swallowed -- inbox files for dead agents
            # are bookkeeping; their removal is not required.
            try:
                inbox_path = _inbox_path(agent_id, args)
                if inbox_path.exists():
                    inbox_path.unlink()
                    record["inbox_removed"] = True
            except OSError:
                pass
        dead_records.append(record)
    return {
        "ok": True,
        "reason": None,
        "alive_count": len(alive),
        "checked": checked,
        "dead": dead_records,
        "skipped_unparseable": skipped,
        "dry_run": dry_run,
    }


# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Obligations CLI helper (used by arm/disarm)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------


def _obligations_cli() -> str | None:
    """Resolve path to the obligations CLI."""
    # Prefer sibling in same bin dir as this script (common dev layout).
    here = Path(__file__).resolve().parent
    candidate = here / "obligations"
    if candidate.exists() and os.access(candidate, os.X_OK):
        return str(candidate)
    import shutil
    found = shutil.which("obligations")
    if found:
        return found
    return None


# Tool patterns that must always pass through, even when the inbox is
# non-empty. Without these, the agent literally cannot ack their own
# inbox -- the ack call itself would be denied by the gate, deadlocking
# the agent. Same shape as the watcher-health gate's exempt list.
#
# Patterns:
#   Bash:^agent-msg ack\b      -- the ack call itself (the recovery path)
#   Bash:^agent-msg inbox\b    -- read-only inspection (always safe)
#   Bash:^agent-msg gc\b       -- explicit garbage collect (read messages)
#   Bash:^agent-msg disarm\b   -- teardown / cleanup
#
# We intentionally do NOT exempt `agent-msg send` (an agent shouldn't be
# sending messages to other agents while gated) or `agent-msg arm` (only
# the main loop arms an agent; subagents have no reason to arm and doing so
# while gated is a smell). Note: arming is no longer solely a separate
# `arm` step -- `cmd_send` auto-arms the inbox gate idempotently on first
# send (see below), so a forgotten `arm` no longer means a delivered-but-
# non-blocking message. There is NO post-tool auto-arm-on-spawn hook; that
# was never implemented.
INBOX_GATE_EXEMPT_PATTERNS = (
    r"Bash:^agent-msg\s+ack\b",
    r"Bash:^agent-msg\s+inbox\b",
    r"Bash:^agent-msg\s+gc\b",
    r"Bash:^agent-msg\s+disarm\b",
)


def _register_inbox_obligation(agent_id: str, inbox_path: Path,
                                ttl_secs: int = DEFAULT_OBLIGATION_TTL_SECS,
                                deny_msg_tag: str | None = None) -> tuple[bool, str]:
    """Register a gate-mode obligation that DENIES all subagent tool calls
    while the inbox is non-empty. The deny banner carries the message body.

    The agent's own ack/inbox/disarm calls are exempted via exempt_patterns
    so the agent can always clear its inbox.

    Returns (ok, ob_id_or_error).
    """
    cli = _obligations_cli()
    if not cli:
        return False, "obligations CLI not found"
    deny_msg = deny_msg_tag or f"{OBLIGATION_TAG_PREFIX}{agent_id}"
    # Belt-and-suspenders agent scoping: the obligation row is only
    # meaningful for THIS agent. Without an `agent_id` param on the
    # `agent_inbox_empty` leaf, a leaked obligation row from a past
    # agent (PostToolUse hook never sees `status=completed`, so the
    # disarm path is dead -- the row just sits at TTL until expiry)
    # would deny every NEW subagent's first tool call with the prior
    # agent's banner (cross-agent leak, 2026-05-03 -- agent A's STOP
    # message surfaced in agent B's deny banner, even though A and B
    # had completely different agent ids). Scoping the leaf via
    # agent_id makes leaked rows benign: they only fire for their
    # owning agent, which by definition has already exited.
    predicate_params = {
        "predicates": [
            {"kind": "is_main_loop", "params": {"negate": True}},
            {"kind": "agent_inbox_empty", "params": {
                "path": str(inbox_path),
                "agent_id": agent_id,
            }},
        ]
    }
    args = [
        cli, "add",
        "--tool-pattern", "*",
        "--predicate", "all_of",
        "--params", json.dumps(predicate_params),
        "--ttl", str(int(ttl_secs)),
        "--enforcement", "gate",
        "--deny-msg", deny_msg,
        "--created-by", f"agent-msg/{agent_id}",
        "--json",
    ]
    for pat in INBOX_GATE_EXEMPT_PATTERNS:
        args += ["--exempt-tool-pattern", pat]
    proc = subprocess.run(args, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=10, check=False)
    if proc.returncode != 0:
        return False, f"obligations add rc={proc.returncode} stderr={proc.stderr.strip()}"
    try:
        result = json.loads(proc.stdout)
        return True, result.get("id", "")
    except json.JSONDecodeError as e:
        return False, f"could not parse obligations add output: {e}"


def _list_obligations() -> list:
    """Read all currently-active obligations via `obligations list --json`."""
    cli = _obligations_cli()
    if not cli:
        return []
    proc = subprocess.run(
        [cli, "list", "--json"],
        capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=10, check=False,
    )
    if proc.returncode != 0:
        return []
    try:
        data = json.loads(proc.stdout)
    except json.JSONDecodeError:
        return []
    return data.get("obligations", []) if isinstance(data, dict) else []


def _remove_inbox_obligations_for_agent(agent_id: str) -> list:
    """Find and `obligations satisfy` every obligation whose deny_message
    matches our tag prefix for this agent. Returns the list of removed ids."""
    tag = f"{OBLIGATION_TAG_PREFIX}{agent_id}"
    cli = _obligations_cli()
    if not cli:
        return []
    removed = []
    for ob in _list_obligations():
        if ob.get("deny_message") == tag:
            ob_id = ob.get("id")
            if not ob_id:
                continue
            proc = subprocess.run(
                [cli, "satisfy", ob_id],
                capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=10, check=False,
            )
            if proc.returncode == 0:
                removed.append(ob_id)
    return removed


# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Subcommand: list / show / index register / index done (existing index ops)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------


def cmd_list(args) -> int:
    index = _read_index()
    if not index:
        print("No agents tracked.")
        return 0
    print(f"{'Agent ID':<40} {'Status':<12} {'Queue Item':<20} {'Description':<40} {'Spawned':<19}")
    print("-" * 131)
    for agent_id, meta in index.items():
        status = meta.get("status", "unknown")
        queue = meta.get("queue_item") or "-"
        desc = meta.get("description", "") or "-"
        if len(desc) > 40:
            desc = desc[:37] + "..."
        spawned = meta.get("spawned_at", "-")
        print(f"{agent_id:<40} {status:<12} {queue:<20} {desc:<40} {spawned:<19}")
    return 0


def cmd_show(args) -> int:
    index = _read_index()
    if args.agent_id not in index:
        print(f"Agent {args.agent_id} not found in index.", file=sys.stderr)
        return 1
    print(json.dumps(index[args.agent_id], indent=2))
    return 0


def cmd_index_register(args) -> int:
    index = _read_index()
    if args.agent_id in index:
        print(f"Agent {args.agent_id} already registered. Use 'done' to clear.",
              file=sys.stderr)
        return 1
    index[args.agent_id] = {
        "agent_id": args.agent_id,
        "status": "running",
        "queue_item": args.queue_item,
        "description": args.description or "",
        "spawned_at": _now_iso(),
        "last_seen": _now_iso(),
    }
    _write_index(index)
    print(f"Registered agent {args.agent_id}")
    return 0


def cmd_index_done(args) -> int:
    index = _read_index()
    if args.agent_id not in index:
        print(f"Agent {args.agent_id} not found in index.", file=sys.stderr)
        return 1
    del index[args.agent_id]
    _write_index(index)
    print(f"Marked agent {args.agent_id} as done.")
    return 0


# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Subcommand: send  -- atomic append to inbox JSON
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------


def cmd_send(args) -> int:
    # Resolution path: if --queue-id is given (and no explicit agent id),
    # resolve it to the single live agent bound to that queue item. LOUD
    # failure on zero / multiple live agents -- never guess (a guess is
    # how corrections got misrouted to the wrong agent's inbox).
    queue_id_arg = getattr(args, "queue_id", None)
    if queue_id_arg:
        if args.agent_id:
            print("ERROR: pass EITHER a positional <agent-id> OR "
                  "--queue-id, not both.", file=sys.stderr)
            return 1
        try:
            args.agent_id = _resolve_queue_id_unique(queue_id_arg, args)
        except ValueError as e:
            if getattr(args, "json", False):
                print(json.dumps({"ok": False, "queue_id": queue_id_arg,
                                  "error": str(e)}, indent=2))
            else:
                print(f"ERROR: {e}", file=sys.stderr)
            return 1
    elif not args.agent_id:
        print("ERROR: send requires a positional <agent-id> or "
              "--queue-id <q-id>.", file=sys.stderr)
        return 1

    agent_id = args.agent_id
    text = args.text
    from_label = args.from_label or "andrew@signal"
    queue_item = args.queue_item
    dry_run = args.dry_run

    inbox_path = _inbox_path(agent_id, args)

    entry = {
        "id": _new_msg_id(),
        "from": from_label,
        "ts": _now_iso(),
        "queue_item": queue_item,
        "text": text,
        "read": False,
        "read_at": None,
    }

    if dry_run:
        print(f"[DRY RUN] Would append to {inbox_path}:")
        print(json.dumps(entry, indent=2))
        return 0

    _ensure_inbox_dir(args)
    fh, messages = _read_inbox_locked(inbox_path)
    try:
        messages.append(entry)
        _write_inbox_locked(fh, messages)
    except Exception:
        _unlock_inbox(fh)
        raise
    try:
        inbox_path.chmod(INBOX_MODE)
    except OSError:
        pass

    # Auto-arm: if no inbox gate obligation exists yet for this agent,
    # register one now so the message actually blocks the subagent. Before
    # this, a `send` without a prior `arm` delivered the message to the
    # inbox file but never registered the gate, so the subagent was never
    # actually blocked (the message sat unread until the agent exited).
    # Idempotent -- skip if a row already exists (explicit `arm` ran first,
    # or a prior `send` already armed). `--no-arm` opts out for the rare
    # test / no-gate case.
    armed_ob_id = None
    if not getattr(args, "no_arm", False):
        tag = f"{OBLIGATION_TAG_PREFIX}{agent_id}"
        already_armed = any(
            ob.get("deny_message") == tag for ob in _list_obligations()
        )
        if not already_armed:
            ok, info = _register_inbox_obligation(agent_id, inbox_path)
            if ok:
                armed_ob_id = info
            else:
                print(f"WARN: auto-arm failed: {info}", file=sys.stderr)

    unread = sum(1 for m in messages if isinstance(m, dict) and not m.get("read"))
    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps({"ok": True, "inbox": str(inbox_path),
                          "auto_armed_obligation": armed_ob_id,
                          "unread": unread, "total": len(messages),
                          "entry": entry}, indent=2))
    else:
        print(f"Appended message to {inbox_path} ({unread} unread / {len(messages)} total)")
    return 0


# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Subcommand: inbox  -- non-destructive read
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------


def cmd_inbox(args) -> int:
    """Read the inbox without consuming. Default: unread only.

    --all           include already-read messages (still GC-trimmed by TTL).
    --json          machine-readable output.
    """
    inbox_path = _inbox_path(args.agent_id, args)
    show_all = bool(getattr(args, "all", False))

    if not inbox_path.exists():
        if args.json:
            print(json.dumps({
                "path": str(inbox_path),
                "messages": [],
                "unread": 0, "total": 0,
                "show_all": show_all,
            }, indent=2))
        else:
            print(f"(no inbox at {inbox_path})")
        return 0

    # Use the locked read path so a v1 inbox is auto-migrated -- this
    # also means a stale read_at gets the current GC pass on first
    # contact. We immediately release the lock since we're not modifying.
    fh, messages = _read_inbox_locked(inbox_path)
    _unlock_inbox(fh)

    unread = [m for m in messages
              if isinstance(m, dict) and not m.get("read")]
    visible = messages if show_all else unread

    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps({
            "path": str(inbox_path),
            "messages": visible,
            "unread": len(unread),
            "total": len(messages),
            "show_all": show_all,
        }, indent=2))
        return 0

    if not visible:
        if show_all:
            print(f"(inbox at {inbox_path} is empty)")
        else:
            if messages:
                print(f"(no unread messages at {inbox_path}; "
                      f"{len(messages)} read message(s) in history -- use --all)")
            else:
                print(f"(inbox at {inbox_path} is empty)")
        return 0

    label = "message(s)" if show_all else "unread message(s)"
    print(f"Inbox: {inbox_path}  ({len(visible)} {label}; "
          f"{len(unread)} unread / {len(messages)} total)")
    for idx, entry in enumerate(visible):
        if not isinstance(entry, dict):
            print(f"  [{idx}] (malformed: {entry!r})")
            continue
        sender = entry.get("from", "?")
        ts = entry.get("ts", "?")
        qi = entry.get("queue_item")
        mid = entry.get("id", "?")
        read_marker = "READ" if entry.get("read") else "UNREAD"
        read_at = entry.get("read_at")
        suffix = f" q={qi}" if qi else ""
        if entry.get("read") and read_at:
            suffix += f" read_at={read_at}"
        print(f"  [{idx}] {read_marker} id={mid} from={sender} ts={ts}{suffix}")
        text = entry.get("text", "")
        for line in (text.splitlines() if isinstance(text, str) else [str(text)]):
            print(f"    {line}")
    return 0


# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Subcommand: ack  -- clear inbox (rewrite to [])
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------


def cmd_ack(args) -> int:
    """Mark UNREAD messages as read; preserve their bodies.

    Default: flips every unread message in the inbox to read=true and
    sets read_at=<now>. Bodies stay on disk so the agent can re-read
    them via `agent-msg inbox --all` until they age out via GC.

    --message-id <id>   ack only the specified message id
    --all-history       also re-stamp read_at for already-read messages
                        (rare; mostly useful for testing)
    """
    inbox_path = _inbox_path(args.agent_id, args)
    _ensure_inbox_dir(args)
    fh, messages = _read_inbox_locked(inbox_path)
    target_id = getattr(args, "message_id", None)
    re_stamp = bool(getattr(args, "all_history", False))
    now = _now_iso()
    flipped = 0
    try:
        for m in messages:
            if not isinstance(m, dict):
                continue
            if target_id is not None and m.get("id") != target_id:
                continue
            if m.get("read"):
                if re_stamp:
                    m["read_at"] = now
                continue
            m["read"] = True
            m["read_at"] = now
            flipped += 1
        _write_inbox_locked(fh, messages)
    except Exception:
        _unlock_inbox(fh)
        raise
    try:
        inbox_path.chmod(INBOX_MODE)
    except OSError:
        pass
    unread = sum(1 for m in messages if isinstance(m, dict) and not m.get("read"))
    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps({
            "ok": True, "inbox": str(inbox_path),
            "flipped": flipped, "unread": unread, "total": len(messages),
            "message_id": target_id,
        }, indent=2))
    else:
        if target_id is not None and flipped == 0:
            print(f"No unread message with id {target_id} at {inbox_path}.")
        else:
            print(f"Marked {flipped} message(s) read at {inbox_path} "
                  f"({unread} unread / {len(messages)} total remain).")
    return 0


# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Subcommand: gc -- explicit garbage-collection of read messages older
# than the TTL. The implicit GC at the top of every CLI invocation does
# the same thing automatically; this is for manual / scripted sweeps.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------


def cmd_gc(args) -> int:
    inbox_path = _inbox_path(args.agent_id, args)
    ttl_hours = getattr(args, "ttl_hours", None)
    if ttl_hours is None:
        ttl_hours = _read_ttl_hours()
    if not inbox_path.exists():
        if args.json:
            print(json.dumps({
                "ok": True, "inbox": str(inbox_path),
                "kept": 0, "dropped": 0, "ttl_hours": ttl_hours,
                "exists": False,
            }, indent=2))
        else:
            print(f"(no inbox at {inbox_path})")
        return 0
    kept, dropped = _gc_inbox_path(inbox_path, ttl_hours=ttl_hours)
    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps({
            "ok": True, "inbox": str(inbox_path),
            "kept": kept, "dropped": dropped, "ttl_hours": ttl_hours,
            "exists": True,
        }, indent=2))
    else:
        print(f"GC at {inbox_path}: kept={kept} dropped={dropped} "
              f"(ttl={ttl_hours}h)")
    return 0


def cmd_gc_dead(args) -> int:
    """Walk inbox obligations; satisfy any whose owning agent is dead.

    Backstop for the broken auto-disarm path: Claude Code's PostToolUse
    hook for the Agent tool fires only on the synchronous-launch reply
    (status="async_launched"), never on actual subagent termination.
    Subagents are async-launched in this codebase, so the disarm branch
    of post-tool-agent-arm-hook never runs and inbox obligations leak
    until the 4h TTL expires. q-0162 made the leaks harmless via
    agent_id scoping, but they still bloat the obligations DB. This
    subcommand sweeps them periodically (cron and/or implicit-on-CLI).
    """
    dry_run = bool(getattr(args, "dry_run", False))
    result = _gc_dead_obligations(dry_run=dry_run, args=args)
    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))
    else:
        if not result["ok"]:
            print(f"gc-dead: skipped ({result['reason']})", file=sys.stderr)
            return 0
        n_dead = len(result["dead"])
        n_satisfied = sum(1 for d in result["dead"] if d["satisfied"])
        n_inbox_removed = sum(1 for d in result["dead"] if d["inbox_removed"])
        prefix = "DRY-RUN " if dry_run else ""
        print(f"{prefix}gc-dead: alive={result['alive_count']} "
              f"checked={result['checked']} dead={n_dead} "
              f"satisfied={n_satisfied} inbox_removed={n_inbox_removed} "
              f"skipped_unparseable={result['skipped_unparseable']}")
        for d in result["dead"]:
            mark = "would-satisfy" if dry_run else (
                "satisfied" if d["satisfied"] else "satisfy-failed")
            print(f"  agent_id={d['agent_id']} ob={d['obligation_id']} {mark}"
                  + (" (inbox removed)" if d["inbox_removed"] else ""))
    return 0


# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Subcommand: arm / disarm  -- per-agent obligation lifecycle
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------


def cmd_arm(args) -> int:
    """Initialise inbox to [] and register gate-mode obligation."""
    inbox_path = _inbox_path(args.agent_id, args)
    _ensure_inbox_dir(args)
    # Initialise inbox idempotently. If it already exists with content,
    # leave it alone -- we don't want to silently drop pending messages
    # on a re-arm.
    fh, existing = _read_inbox_locked(inbox_path)
    try:
        if not existing:
            _write_inbox_locked(fh, [])
        else:
            _unlock_inbox(fh)
    except Exception:
        _unlock_inbox(fh)
        raise
    try:
        inbox_path.chmod(INBOX_MODE)
    except OSError:
        pass

    # Register obligation (skipped in test mode where --no-obligation is set).
    ob_id = ""
    if not args.no_obligation:
        ok, info = _register_inbox_obligation(args.agent_id, inbox_path,
                                              ttl_secs=args.ttl)
        if not ok:
            print(f"ERROR registering obligation: {info}", file=sys.stderr)
            return 1
        ob_id = info

    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps({
            "ok": True,
            "agent_id": args.agent_id,
            "inbox": str(inbox_path),
            "obligation_id": ob_id,
        }, indent=2))
    else:
        print(f"Armed agent {args.agent_id}: inbox={inbox_path} obligation={ob_id or '(skipped)'}")
    return 0


def cmd_disarm(args) -> int:
    """Clear inbox + remove any inbox obligations for this agent."""
    inbox_path = _inbox_path(args.agent_id, args)
    cleared_inbox = False
    if inbox_path.exists():
        _ensure_inbox_dir(args)
        fh, _ = _read_inbox_locked(inbox_path)
        try:
            _write_inbox_locked(fh, [])
            cleared_inbox = True
        except Exception:
            _unlock_inbox(fh)
            raise
        # Also remove the file entirely on disarm (cleaner state).
        try:
            inbox_path.unlink()
        except OSError:
            pass

    removed = []
    if not args.no_obligation:
        removed = _remove_inbox_obligations_for_agent(args.agent_id)

    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps({
            "ok": True,
            "agent_id": args.agent_id,
            "inbox_cleared": cleared_inbox,
            "obligations_removed": removed,
        }, indent=2))
    else:
        print(f"Disarmed agent {args.agent_id}: cleared_inbox={cleared_inbox} "
              f"obligations_removed={removed}")
    return 0


