    """Regression (q-2026-06-24-fd10): the gc-dead liveness query MUST pass a
    large --max-age-seconds so a subagent quiet for >120s (long thinking pass /
    slow tool call) is NOT classed dead and reaped out from under itself.

    A fake claude-watch records the argv it was invoked with; we assert
    --max-age-seconds is present and well above claude-watch's own 120s
    default, and that the parsed alive set still comes back correctly.
